{
  "doc_id": "3934",
  "text": "We wanted to check if a model taking into account motif multiplicity would allow a more precise prediction of the value of expression. Therefore, we applied a linear regression analysis to the motifs identified by BN analysis as significant in both systems, and additionally the motif SATB significant in the MCAO system only. For the reasons detailed in the Materials and methods, we always performed a weighted linear regression, with the average loadings in groups of genes with the same motif count as the response variable, and the weights set to the numbers of genes in each group, as suggested by Faraway [CITATION_1] .",
